# GROW-AI — Complete API & Service Setup Guide

Your project uses **15 external services** + **3 self-hosted Docker services**. Here's everything you need to set up, organized by priority.

---

## Quick Overview

| # | Service | Feature | Free? | Monthly Cost (Paid) | Priority |
|---|---------|---------|-------|---------------------|----------|
| 1 | **PostgreSQL** (Docker) | Database | ✅ Self-hosted | Free | 🔴 Required |
| 2 | **Redis** (Docker) | Job queue (BullMQ) | ✅ Self-hosted | Free | 🔴 Required |
| 3 | **Qdrant** (Docker) | Vector DB for RAG chat | ✅ Self-hosted | Free | 🔴 Required |
| 4 | **Google Gemini** | Core AI engine | ✅ Free tier | Pay-per-use after | 🔴 Required |
| 5 | **Upstash Redis** | Rate limiting / caching | ✅ 10k req/day | $0.2/100k commands | 🔴 Required |
| 6 | **NextAuth / JWT** | Authentication | ✅ Free (library) | Free | 🔴 Required |
| 7 | **Google OAuth** | Google login + YouTube | ✅ Free | Free | 🟡 Optional |
| 8 | **Cloudinary** | Image/video hosting & CDN | ✅ 25 credits/mo | ~$89/mo (Plus) | 🟡 Optional |
| 9 | **Resend** | Email campaigns | ✅ 100 emails/day | $20/mo (Pro) | 🟡 Optional |
| 10 | **Twilio** | Voice call infrastructure | 🟡 Trial credits | ~$0.013/min | 🟡 Optional |
| 11 | **Ultravox** | AI voice conversation engine | ❓ Contact sales | Varies | 🟡 Optional |
| 12 | **Replicate** | AI video generation | ❌ Pay-per-use | ~$0.032/sec (GPU) | 🟡 Optional |
| 13 | **Bannerbear** | Marketing banner generation | 🟡 Trial only | $49/mo (Starter) | 🟡 Optional |
| 14 | **Instagram (Meta)** | Social integration | ✅ Free | Free | ⚪ Optional |
| 15 | **LinkedIn** | Social integration | ✅ Free | Free | ⚪ Optional |
| 16 | **UploadThing** | File uploads | ✅ 2GB free | $10/mo (Pro) | ⚪ Not actively used |

---

## 🔴 REQUIRED — App Won't Start Without These

### 1. PostgreSQL, Redis, Qdrant (Docker)

**What they do:** PostgreSQL is the main database, Redis powers the BullMQ job queue (document processing), Qdrant is the vector database for RAG-based AI chat.

**Cost:** Free (self-hosted via Docker)

**Setup:**
1. Install [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/)
2. Run: `docker-compose up -d db redis qdrant`
3. This starts PostgreSQL on `:5432`, Redis on `:6379`, Qdrant on `:6333`
4. Run database migrations:
   ```bash
   npx prisma generate
   npx prisma db push
   ```

**Env vars (already set):**
```env
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:mysecretpassword@localhost:5432/flowai"
QDRANT_URL="http://localhost:6333"
```

---

### 2. Google Gemini API

**What it does:** Powers ALL AI features — content generation, chat assistant, email copy, product photo generation, video scene generation, competitor analysis, business planning.

**Cost:** ✅ Free tier (15 RPM, 1M tokens/day for Flash models). Paid: $0.075/1M input tokens for Gemini 2.0 Flash.

**Used in:** [video-action.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/video/video-action.ts), [GenerateEmails.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/mailMarketing/GenerateEmails.ts), [chat/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/chat/route.ts), [content-generator/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/dashboard/content-generator/route.ts), `competiotionAnalysis/`, `business-planner/`, photoshoot page  
**Models used:** `gemini-2.0-flash`, `gemini-2.0-flash-exp-image-generation`, `gemini-1.5-flash`

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey)
2. Sign in with your Google account
3. Click **"Create API Key"**
4. Copy the key

**Env var:**
```env
GEMINI_API_KEY="your-gemini-api-key"
```

---

### 3. Upstash Redis

**What it does:** Rate limiting on API routes (e.g., video generation is limited to 2 requests per 30 seconds). Separate from the Docker Redis which handles job queues.

**Cost:** ✅ Free tier: 10,000 commands/day, 256MB storage. Paid: $0.2 per 100k commands.

**Used in:** [video-action.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/video/video-action.ts) (rate limiting via `@upstash/ratelimit`)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Upstash Console](https://console.upstash.com/)
2. Create a free account
3. Click **"Create Database"** → Select region closest to you → Choose **Free** plan
4. After creation, copy the **REST URL** and **REST Token** from the dashboard

**Env vars:**
```env
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL="https://xxx.upstash.io"
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN="AXxxxx..."
```

---

### 4. NextAuth Secret

**What it does:** Signs JWT tokens for user authentication. This is just a random secret string, not an external API.

**Cost:** Free

**Setup:**
```bash
openssl rand -base64 32
```

**Env vars:**
```env
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="<paste-generated-secret>"
```

---

## 🟡 OPTIONAL — Enable Specific Features

### 5. Google OAuth (Google Login + YouTube Integration)

**What it does:** Allows users to sign in with Google. Also required for YouTube channel integration (analytics, connecting YouTube accounts).

**Cost:** ✅ Free

**Used in:** [auth.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/auth.ts) (login), [social/youtube/auth/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/social/youtube/auth/route.ts) (YouTube)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Create a new project (or use existing)
3. Navigate to **APIs & Services → Credentials**
4. Click **"Create Credentials" → "OAuth Client ID"**
5. Application type: **Web application**
6. Add **Authorized redirect URIs:**
   - `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google`
   - `http://localhost:3000/api/social/youtube/callback`
7. Copy the **Client ID** and **Client Secret**
8. Enable these APIs in **APIs & Services → Library:**
   - YouTube Data API v3
   - YouTube Analytics API

**Env vars:**
```env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="xxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com"
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="GOCSPX-xxxx"
YOUTUBE_REDIRECT_URL="http://localhost:3000/api/social/youtube/callback"
```

---

### 6. Cloudinary

**What it does:** Hosts and processes images/videos. Used for product photoshoot uploads, AI video storage, content image hosting, and fallback slideshow creation.

**Cost:** ✅ Free tier: 25 credits/mo (~25 transformations + 1GB storage). Paid: Plus plan at ~$89/mo.

**Used in:** [video-action.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/video/video-action.ts) (video hosting), [content-generator/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/dashboard/content-generator/route.ts) (content images), [newVideo.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/video/newVideo.ts) (video URL hosting)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Cloudinary](https://cloudinary.com/) → Sign up
2. After signup, go to your **Dashboard**
3. Copy **Cloud Name**, **API Key**, and **API Secret** from the dashboard

**Env vars:**
```env
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME="dxxxxxxxxx"
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY="123456789012345"
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET="xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
```

---

### 7. Resend (Email Marketing)

**What it does:** Sends AI-generated personalized and bulk marketing emails to leads uploaded via CSV.

**Cost:** ✅ Free tier: 100 emails/day, 1 domain. Paid: $20/mo (5k emails/mo, custom domains).

**Used in:** [GenerateEmails.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/mailMarketing/GenerateEmails.ts) (both generic and personalized email campaigns)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Resend](https://resend.com/) → Sign up
2. Navigate to **API Keys** → Create a new key
3. To send from a custom domain (not `onboarding@resend.dev`):
   - Go to **Domains** → Add your domain
   - Add the DNS records Resend provides (DKIM, SPF, DMARC)

**Env vars:**
```env
RESEND_API_KEY="re_xxxxxxxxxxxx"
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL="marketing@yourdomain.com"
RESEND_REPLY_TO_EMAIL="hello@yourdomain.com"
```

---

### 8. Twilio (Voice Call Infrastructure)

**What it does:** Makes actual phone calls for voice sales campaigns. Works with Ultravox to connect AI voice agents to real phone calls.

**Cost:** 🟡 Trial: $15.50 credit (enough for ~100 test calls). Paid: ~$0.013/min outbound, $1/mo per phone number.

**Used in:** [startCampaign.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/voice-agent/startCampaign.ts) (creating calls, tracking status)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Twilio](https://www.twilio.com/) → Sign up
2. Verify your phone number
3. From the **Console Dashboard**, copy your **Account SID** and **Auth Token**
4. Buy a phone number: **Phone Numbers → Buy a Number** → Get a local number

**Env vars:**
```env
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID="ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN="xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER="+1234567890"
```

---

### 9. Ultravox (AI Voice Agent)

**What it does:** Powers the conversational AI voice agent that talks to customers on calls. Creates an AI-driven voice conversation via Twilio's stream.

**Cost:** ❓ Contact for pricing. The service is relatively new and pricing may vary.

**Used in:** [startCampaign.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/voice-agent/startCampaign.ts) (creating AI call sessions, fetching transcripts)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Ultravox](https://www.ultravox.ai/)
2. Sign up / request API access
3. Once approved, get your API key from the dashboard

**Env vars:**
```env
ULTRAVOX_API_KEY="your-ultravox-api-key"
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Twilio and Ultravox work together. Both are needed for the voice agent feature. Without either, voice campaigns won't work.

---

### 10. Replicate (AI Video Generation)

**What it does:** Generates marketing videos from product images using AI models (specifically `minimax/video-01-director`). Videos are then uploaded to Cloudinary.

**Cost:** ❌ Pay-per-use only. ~$0.032/sec of GPU time. A typical video generation could cost $0.50-$2.00.

**Used in:** [actions/video/newVideo.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/actions/video/newVideo.ts), [app/actions/video/newVideo.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/actions/video/newVideo.ts)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Replicate](https://replicate.com/) → Sign up with GitHub
2. Navigate to **Account Settings → API Tokens**
3. Create a new token

**Env vars:**
```env
REPLICATE_API_TOKEN="r8_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
```

> [!NOTE]
> Replicate requires a payment method after your free credits are used. The `minimax/video-01-director` model is used for video generation.

---

### 11. Bannerbear (Marketing Banner Generation)

**What it does:** Generates professional marketing banners/images for content posts using pre-designed templates. Used in the content generator feature.

**Cost:** 🟡 Free trial available (limited images). Paid: $49/mo Starter (100 images), $149/mo Business (500 images).

**Used in:** [content-generator/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/dashboard/content-generator/route.ts) (generating images for blog posts, social media, ads)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Bannerbear](https://www.bannerbear.com/) → Sign up
2. Create a **Project** → Design a **Template** (or use a pre-made one)
3. Copy the template ID (currently hardcoded as `1eGqK9b3zPgwDnaYpP` in the code — you'll need your own)
4. Go to **Settings → API Key** → Copy your key

**Env vars:**
```env
BANNERBEAR_API_KEY="bb_pr_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
```

> [!WARNING]
> The code uses a hardcoded template ID `1eGqK9b3zPgwDnaYpP`. You'll need to create your own template in Bannerbear and update this ID in [app/api/dashboard/content-generator/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/dashboard/content-generator/route.ts) (line 396).

---

### 12. Instagram (Meta) Integration

**What it does:** Connects user Instagram accounts to view profile data, media, and post analytics. Uses Instagram Basic Display API.

**Cost:** ✅ Free

**Used in:** [social/instagram/auth/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/social/instagram/auth/route.ts), [social/instagram/data/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/social/instagram/data/route.ts)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [Meta for Developers](https://developers.facebook.com/) → Create a developer account
2. Click **"Create App"** → Choose **"Consumer"** type
3. Add **"Instagram Basic Display"** product to your app
4. Under **Instagram Basic Display → Basic Display Settings:**
   - Add **Valid OAuth Redirect URIs:** `http://localhost:3000/api/social/instagram/callback`
   - Add **Deauthorize Callback URL** and **Data Deletion Request URL**
5. Under **App Roles → Instagram Testers**, add your Instagram account as a tester
6. On Instagram, go to **Settings → Apps & Websites → Tester Invites** and accept

**Env vars:**
```env
INSTAGRAM_APP_ID="123456789012345"
INSTAGRAM_APP_SECRET="xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
INSTAGRAM_REDIRECT_URI="http://localhost:3000/api/social/instagram/callback"
```

---

### 13. LinkedIn Integration

**What it does:** Connects user LinkedIn accounts for social media analytics and potential content publishing.

**Cost:** ✅ Free

**Used in:** [social/linkedin/auth/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/social/linkedin/auth/route.ts), [social/linkedin/data/route.ts](file:///Users/harshsmac/GROW-AI/app/api/social/linkedin/data/route.ts)

**Setup:**
1. Go to [LinkedIn Developers](https://www.linkedin.com/developers/) → Create an app
2. Under the **Auth** tab:
   - Copy **Client ID** and **Client Secret**
   - Add **Redirect URL:** `http://localhost:3000/api/social/linkedin/callback`
3. Under **Products** tab, request access to:
   - **Share on LinkedIn** (for `w_member_social` scope)
   - **Sign In with LinkedIn using OpenID Connect** (for `openid email profile` scopes)

**Env vars:**
```env
LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID="xxxxxxxxxxxx"
LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET="xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI="http://localhost:3000/api/social/linkedin/callback"
```

---

## ⚪ NOT ACTIVELY USED

### 14. UploadThing

**Status:** Package is installed (`@uploadthing/react`, `uploadthing`) but **no code references were found** in the project. It may be planned for future use or was replaced by direct Cloudinary uploads.

**If you decide to use it later:**
- Go to [UploadThing](https://uploadthing.com/) → Sign up → Create an app
- Free tier: 2GB storage, $10/mo for Pro

---

## Summary: Minimum Viable Setup

To get the app running with core features, you need **only 4 things:**

| Step | Service | Time |
|------|---------|------|
| 1 | Docker (PostgreSQL + Redis + Qdrant) | 5 min |
| 2 | Google Gemini API key | 2 min |
| 3 | Upstash Redis account | 5 min |
| 4 | Generate NEXTAUTH_SECRET | 1 min |

**Total: ~13 minutes** to get the basic app running with AI chat, content generation, business planning, and competitor analysis.

For the full experience (voice, email, video, social integrations), add the optional services as needed based on which features you want to test.
